						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the central shrine in the Chandramauḷīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśivarāya. Ś. 1461 (wrong for Ś. 1465: 1543 A.D.)</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1461, Śōbhakṛit. The Śaka year cited appears to be a mistake for 1465. The epigraph stops after citing the above date.</p>						

						<p>It mentions Sadāśiva-mahārāya as the son of Vīrapratāpa Raṅgayadēva who was pleased to witness the [elephant]-hunt.</p>						

						</summary>
